Abiodun Nejo, Ado Ekiti Ekiti State Governor and Chairman, Nigeria Governors’ Forum, Dr Kayode Fayemi, has reassured Nigerians and the people of the state that he is okay and will come out of isolation hale and hearty. Fayemi, who on Wednesday announced that the result of his third COVID-19 test came back positive following which he self-isolated, thanked Nigerians for the love and solidarity expressed to him over the matter, saying he would soon return to his desk. The governor, in a video message released by his aides in Ado Ekiti on Thursday, said, “I shall come out of this healthy and physically back on duty to render services to Ekiti.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 